Enum EventStrategy.Detachment

  • java.lang.Object

      • org.apache.tinkerpop.gremlin.process.traversal.strategy.decoration.EventStrategy.Detachment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Enclosing class:
    EventStrategy

    public static enum EventStrategy.Detachment
extends Enum<EventStrategy.Detachment>
implements EventStrategy.Detacher
    Options for detaching elements from the graph during eventing.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      DETACHED_NO_PROPERTIES
      Uses DetachedFactory to detach and does not include properties of elements that have them.
      DETACHED_WITH_PROPERTIES
      Uses DetachedFactory to detach and includes properties of elements that have them.
      NONE
      Does not detach the element from the graph.
      REFERENCE
      Uses ReferenceFactory to detach which only includes id and label of elements.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • NONE

        public static final EventStrategy.Detachment NONE
        Does not detach the element from the graph. It should be noted that if this option is used with transactional graphs new transactions may be opened if these elements are accessed after a commit() is called.

      • DETACHED_WITH_PROPERTIES

        public static final EventStrategy.Detachment DETACHED_WITH_PROPERTIES

      • DETACHED_NO_PROPERTIES

        public static final EventStrategy.Detachment DETACHED_NO_PROPERTIES
        Uses DetachedFactory to detach and does not include properties of elements that have them.

      • REFERENCE

        public static final EventStrategy.Detachment REFERENCE
        Uses ReferenceFactory to detach which only includes id and label of elements.
